# LiVEiT® Image Guidance

Images are an important part of the LiVEiT® visual identity.

Photography, illustrations and supporting graphics should reinforce the principles of clarity, accessibility and professionalism that define the LiVEiT® Framework.

Images should enhance communication rather than distract from it.

---

# Visual Style

Official LiVEiT® imagery should feel:

* Clean
* Modern
* Professional
* Authentic
* Inclusive
* Calm
* Purposeful

Every image should support the content it accompanies.

---

# Photography

Whenever possible, photography should be:

* High resolution
* Naturally lit
* Well composed
* Free from unnecessary visual clutter
* Relevant to the subject matter

Authentic photography is preferred over heavily staged or any Ai imagery.

---

# Subject Matter

Images should reflect the purpose of the LiVEiT® Framework.

Suitable subjects include:

* Technology
* Collaboration
* Healthcare
* Education
* Innovation
* Community
* Accessibility
* Digital environments

Supporting imagery should communicate understanding, connection and progress.

---

# Illustrations

Illustrations should follow the same design principles as the wider LiVEiT® brand.

They should be:

* Simple
* Consistent
* Modern
* Easy to understand

Illustrations should complement the interface without overwhelming it.

---

# Background Images

Background images should remain subtle.

They should never reduce the readability of:

* Logos
* Headings
* Body text
* Navigation
* Interface controls

Where necessary, overlays or transparency effects may be used to improve contrast.

---

# Colour

Images should work harmoniously with the official LiVEiT® colour palette.

Avoid imagery that introduces conflicting colour schemes or distracts from the primary branding.

Where appropriate, the Aqua brand colour (`#7EBECD`) may be used as a subtle accent within supporting graphics.

---

# Image Quality

Only high quality images should be used.

Avoid:

* Pixelated images
* Blurred photographs
* Heavy compression
* Visible artefacts
* Low-resolution screenshots

Professional presentation supports confidence in the LiVEiT® brand.

---

# Accessibility

Images should be accessible to all users.

Where appropriate:

* Provide descriptive alternative text.
* Avoid placing important information within images alone.
* Ensure sufficient contrast between images and overlaid text.
* Use captions where they improve understanding.

Images should support accessibility rather than create barriers.

---

# Diversity and Inclusion

Imagery should reflect a broad range of people, experiences and environments.

Official LiVEiT® materials should present individuals with dignity, authenticity and respect.

Representation should feel natural rather than tokenistic.

---

# Decorative Graphics

Decorative graphics should remain secondary to the content.

Avoid excessive visual effects or unnecessary ornamentation that distracts from the user experience.

Whitespace is an important part of the LiVEiT® design language and should be preserved.

---

# Artificial Intelligence

AI generated imagery may be used where appropriate, provided it meets the same standards of quality, professionalism and accuracy as traditional photography or illustration.

Content creators remain responsible for ensuring that generated imagery accurately represents the intended subject and complies with applicable copyright, licensing and ethical requirements.

---

# Best Practice

When selecting imagery:

* Prioritise clarity.
* Use high quality assets.
* Support the surrounding content.
* Maintain accessibility.
* Preserve visual consistency.
* Respect the LiVEiT® brand identity.

Well-chosen imagery strengthens communication while reinforcing the professional appearance of the LiVEiT® Framework.
